“community nurse” means a person who holds a certificate certifying 
that  such  person  has  undergone  a  course  of  training  for  community 
nurses and passed the examination conducted by the Board;

“emergency” means a sudden unforeseen event occurring during the 
course  of  pregnancy,  childbirth,  and  puerperium  needing  prompt 
intervention to save the life of the mother or child;

“rural health nurse” means a person who holds a certificate certifying 
that  such  person  has  undergone  a  course  of  training  for  rural  health 
nurses and passed the examination conducted by the Board;

